Filters are convoluted and difficult. In some places they are &#39;filter 
out&#39;.  In other places they are &#39;filter in&#39;.  Sometimes their 
interpretation can be flipped, etc.   This needs to be addressed (A 
while back we sent a note to the list on a way to address filters inside 
scope: http://groups.yahoo.com/group/archive-crawler/message/337).

What you&#39;re asking to do in the below should be straight-forward and 
obvious, but its not.  It took a few of us a while sitting together 
around a screen to figure how to do what you want. 

You need to use the FilterScope (You choose scopes in the &#39;Module&#39; 
page).  After selecting this scope, add to it a regex filter by browsing 
to the Filter tab.  Once added, return to the settings screen. The 
FilterScope regex shows in a non-obvious position below the &#39;excluding&#39; 
pathdepth and pathological filters.  Into the regex, fill a regex 
pattern that will allow the desired URLs AND robots and dns.  Using your 
example below where you want all URLs with a &#39;reg1&#39; substring, you&#39;d 
use: &quot;^(dns:.*|.*reg1.*|.*robots.txt)$&quot;.

St.Ack


